(1, 'Welcome to IsDB-BISEW', NULL, 'about', '<h3 class=\"heading3\">The Management and Administration of IsDB-BISEW</h3>\r\n<p>The management and administration of the IsDB-BISEW has been vested on a Committee of Mutawallis constituted by six members of which, three members represent the Government of Bangladesh while the other three members come from the Islamic Development Bank.</p>\r\n<p>The office of IsDB-BISEW is responsible for management and administration, planning and implementation of the projects and also for operation and management of wakf properties and assets.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"heading3\">Formation of Committee of Mutawallis</h3>\r\n<p>The Committee of Mutawallis shall consist of a Chairman, a Vice-Chairman and four other members. The Chairman and Vice-Chairman shall be nominated by the Bank and the Government by rotation so that if in any particular term the Chairman is nominated by the Bank, the Vice-Chairman shall, for that term, be nominated by the Government and if for any particular term the Chairman is nominated by the Government, the Vice-Chairman shall, for that term, be nominated by the Bank. Of the four other members, two will be nominated by the Bank and the other two will be nominated by the Government. The tenure of the Committee is for 3 (three) years.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"heading3\">The objectives and purposes of IsDB-BISEW</h3>\r\n<p>IsDB-BISEW undertakes funding, formulating and implementing of projects in the areas of education, human resource development and institutional strengthening.</p>\r\n<p>The intent is to gradually transform the large population into productive workforce by strengthening their technical capability to use existing and emerging technologies resulting in sustainable economic growth and equality.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"heading3\">Resources of IsDB-BISEW</h3>\r\n<p>IsDB-BISEW generates its revenue by renting out commercial spaces of IDB Bhaban, a 20-storied building and a 4-storied shopping complex.</p>\r\n<p>IDB Bhaban has become the &ldquo;land mark&rdquo; of Dhaka city because of the best possible tenants under one roof and establishing one of a kind of computer market in the shopping complex. Highest standard of operation and management of the complex in order to retain international, multinational organizations to ensure uninterrupted flow of rental income so to maintain projects operation pursuing IsDB-BISEW&rsquo;s objectives.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>', NULL, 'Islamic Development Bank-Bangladesh Islamic Solidarity Educational Wakf (IsDB-BISEW) was established following an agreement between the Islamic Development Bank, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, and the Government of Bangladesh.', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'page', 'individual', 'from_old', 'photos/shares/2019-09/15_1567675841.jpg', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1, '2019-09-05 09:30:42', '2019-11-03 08:28:41'),
(2, 'IT Scholarship Programme Objective', NULL, 'it-scholarship-programme-objective', '<p>The purpose of the project is to provide scholarship to underprivileged but meritorious Muslim Youths to undergo extensive training for development of employable skills in the field of Information and Communication Technology (ICT). These unemployed graduates possess enormous potential which could not yet be properly exploited due to lack of finance.</p>\r\n<h3 class=\"heading3\">Who can apply for the IT Scholarship Programme?</h3>\r\n<p>Candidates who have a strong desire to build themselves up as IT professionals but do not have the financial means to pay for the required training. They must have the following academic backgrounds:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelors/Fazil degree holders.</li>\r\n<li>Diploma holders in Civil/Architecture/ Construction/Surveying/Computer Technology/Computer Science or Telecommunication Engineering or Electronics Engineering.</li>\r\n<li>Candidates must have at least second division or GPA 2.0 results in their SSC and HSC examinations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><a class=\"btn btn-main\" href=\"http://apply.idb-bisew.info/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Apply Online</a></p>', NULL, 'The purpose of the project is to provide scholarship to underprivileged but meritorious Muslim Youths to undergo extensive training for development of employable skills in the field of Information and Communication Technology (ICT).', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'page', 'it-scholarship-programme', 'from_old', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 3, '2019-09-08 04:46:00', '2019-11-25 04:22:02'),
(3, 'IT Scholarship Programme Overview', NULL, 'it-scholarship-programme-overview', '<p>The purpose of the project is to provide scholarship to underprivileged but meritorious Muslim Youths to undergo extensive training for development of employable skills in the field of Information and Communication Technology (ICT). These unemployed graduates possess enormous potential which could not yet be properly exploited due to lack of finance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Each year around 1,200 young graduates from widely varying academic backgrounds are awarded scholarship by IsDB-BISEW in Bangladesh. A joint initiative of the Govt. of Bangladesh and IDB, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, the scholarship programme enables the participants to undergo a year-long training leading to a professional level diploma in an IT discipline. These diploma holders then go on to secure excellent jobs and rewarding careers in organizations both within and outside Bangladesh.</p>\r\n<p>The IsDB-BISEW IT Scholarship Programme is an educational and training network composed of approximately twenty-five IT training institutions, a full-scale R &amp; D cell dedicated for developing training-resources and curriculum and an administrative body headed by the management office of IDB-BISEW. Full-time and intensive training programmes training from 10 to 14 months in duration equip the trainees with cutting edge IT skills, which in the vast majority of cases lead to rewarding careers in various organizations at home and abroad.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>IT Professional Diploma</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Architectural and Civil CAD</li>\r\n<li>Database Design and Development</li>\r\n<li>Graphics, Animation &amp; Video Editing</li>\r\n<li>Enterprise Systems Analysis and Design-JEE</li>\r\n<li>Enterprise Systems Analysis and Design-C#</li>\r\n<li>Networking Technologies</li>\r\n<li>Web Application Development with PHP and Frameworks</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a class=\"btn btn-success\" href=\"http://www.idb-bisew.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=15&amp;Itemid=10\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Course Details</a></p>', NULL, 'Each year around 1,200 young graduates from widely varying academic backgrounds are awarded scholarship by IDB-BISEW in Bangladesh. A joint initiative of the Govt. of Bangladesh and IDB, Jeddah, Saudi Arabia, the scholarship programme enables the participants to undergo a year-long training leading to a professional level diploma in an IT discipline.', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'page', 'it-scholarship-programme', 'off', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 3, '2019-09-08 09:52:00', '2019-11-25 04:21:33'),
(4, 'IT Scholarship Programme Outcome', NULL, 'it-scholarship-programme-outcome', '<p>The IsDB-BISEW IT Scholarship Programme is producing internationally competitive IT professionals who continue to be readily absorbed by employers in the ICT and related employment sectors. This landmark project is securing exciting careers for its graduates and bringing about dramatic transformation in the lives of thousands of youths who otherwise would have been just another group of data points in the annual unemployment statistics of our country.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Outstanding placement record with graduates employed both within and outside the country.</li>\r\n<li>The IsDB-BISEW IT Scholarship Programme has so far placed 6,280 high-end it professional in jobs</li>\r\n<li>The project offers a full-fledged placement cell with its own website</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Project Datasheet</h3>\r\n<table class=\"table table-bordered table-striped\" style=\"height: 198px;\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Project inception</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">2003</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Intake<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Rounds</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">45</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Application received<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(up to Round &ndash; 44)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">152,910</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Appeared in Aptitude Test (up to Round &ndash; 44)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">126,228</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Candidates interviewed<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(up to Round &ndash; 44)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">121,487</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Scholarship Awarded<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(up to Round &ndash; 44)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">13,759</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Computer Literacy Program (up to Round &ndash; 43)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">10,513</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">High-end IT Professionals<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(up to Round &ndash; 39)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">7,085</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Job Placement<strong>&nbsp;</strong>(as on 15 November 2019)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">6,280</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\">Rounds in Progress (40 &ndash; 44)</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">1,060</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr style=\"height: 18px;\">\r\n<td style=\"height: 18px; width: 336px;\"># of organizations employing project graduates</td>\r\n<td style=\"text-align: center; height: 18px; width: 117px;\">More than 1,525</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>', NULL, 'This landmark project is securing exciting careers for its graduates and bringing about dramatic transformation in the lives of thousands of youths who otherwise would have been just another group of data points in the annual unemployment statistics of our country.', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'page', 'it-scholarship-programme', 'off', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 3, '2019-09-08 10:01:00', '2019-11-25 04:19:20'),
(5, 'IT Scholarship Unique Features', NULL, 'it-scholarship-unique-features', '<h3>Features</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>100% free of cost</li>\r\n<li>Industry relevant training content</li>\r\n<li>Open and merit based selection of targeted and deserving candidates</li>\r\n<li>Close &amp; constant monitoring of training delivery</li>\r\n<li>Practical competency-based performance assessment of trainees</li>\r\n<li>Continuous assessment via Quiz &amp; Evidence-based tests</li>\r\n<li>Project-based learning</li>\r\n<li>Industry recognized international certification exam</li>\r\n<li>Intervention-free web-based invoicing system for TSPs and the Project Consultant (PC)</li>\r\n<li>Payments to TSPs and PC directly linked to trainees&rsquo; performance</li>\r\n<li>Accountability of all stakeholders</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Benefits</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Opportunity to achieve a professional IT career in only one year</li>\r\n<li>The quickest route to financial independence</li>\r\n<li>Achieve international recognition of skills through Vendor Certification</li>\r\n<li>Guaranteed job placement</li>\r\n<li>The best of the best IT professional training available in Bangladesh</li>\r\n<li>Completely free with no hidden cost involved</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'page', 'it-scholarship-programme', 'off', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 3, '2019-09-08 10:14:00', '2019-11-25 04:48:38'),
(6, 'Training and Assessment', NULL, 'training-and-assessment', '<p><strong>Classes Sessions:</strong>&nbsp; Class sessions last for four hours each day, six days a week. Lesson delivery is through instructor-led sessions. The first two hours of the session, termed as &ldquo;Contact Sessions&rdquo;, emphasis principles and theoretical aspects of the competency being taught. The subsequent two hours of the class, known as &ldquo;Hands-on Sessions&rdquo; allows the trainee to carry out hands-on exercise on the topic(s) of the Contact session under the supervision of the instructor.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Assessment:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>All courses in the Programme include a structured series of assessment exercises that measure a trainee&rsquo;s level of understanding of the lessons learnt and also his/her ability to perform the skills in a practical environment. The guiding principles and procedures employed in implementing the assessments are enumerated below.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Separation of Concerns:</strong>&nbsp; An essential attribute of all courses in the IsDB-BISEW IT Scholarship Programme is that the party delivering the training is distinct from the party conducting the final assessment. The Training Service Providers (TSPs) are responsible for delivering the day-to-day training while it is the PA and the PC who carry out the final assessment. This operating principle ensures that the trainee&rsquo;s performance at the end of the training is valid and credible.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Relevance for the Workplace:&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>Assessment for each course consists of particular combinations of units of competency that have been grouped to support the development of identified sets of competencies. Workers in ordinary work scenarios require these sets of competencies.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Non-negotiable:</strong>&nbsp; When assessment is conducted according to the assessment guidelines and when the evidence collected satisfies the performance criteria in the competency standards, then the Programme Consultant will recommend that the trainee be allowed to proceed to the next course component. The competency standards, the assessment guidelines and the specification for qualifications are non-negotiable components for training programs under the IsDB-BISEW programme.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Competency-based Assessment:&nbsp;</strong>The IsDB-BISEW IT Scholarship Programme has adopted a competency-based approach to assess and report trainee&rsquo;s achievements in all of its training programmes. This means that trainee achievement is assessed and reported against industry competency standards as prescribed in the Delivery and Assessment Guide (DAG) provided to the TSPs. Industry competency standards describe the tasks performed by competent workers in the workplace. Competence incorporates all aspects of work performance, including problem solving and the capacity to apply skills and knowledge in both familiar and new situations.</p>', NULL, 'Class sessions last for four hours each day, six days a week. Lesson delivery is through instructor-led sessions. The first two hours of the session, termed as “Contact Sessions”, emphasis principles and theoretical aspects of the competency being taught. The subsequent two hours of the class, known as “Hands-on Sessions”', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'page', 'it-scholarship-programme', 'off', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 3, '2019-09-08 10:20:00', '2019-11-25 04:23:42'),
(7, 'The candidate must have adequate proficiency in using engineering software particularly Auto-CAD.', NULL, 'the-candidate-must-have-adequate-proficiency-in-using-engineering-software-particularly', '<p><strong>Qualification and Experience:</strong>&nbsp;Diploma Engineer (Civil) having 15 years experience, of which, minimum 5 years experience in maintenance of high-rise commercial building. The candidate must have adequate proficiency in using engineering software particularly Auto-CAD.</p>\r\n<p><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.idb-bisew.org/images/stories/Administrative/Vacancies/July19/ad_2019.png\" /><span style=\"color: #2f2f2f; font-family: Tahoma, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px;\"><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.idb-bisew.org/images/stories/Administrative/Vacancies/July19/ad_2019_web.png\" /><span style=\"color: #2f2f2f; font-family: Tahoma, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 11px;\"><br /></span></p>', NULL, 'Diploma Engineer (Civil) having 15 years experience, of which, minimum 5 years experience in maintenance of high-rise commercial building. The candidate must have adequate proficiency in using engineering software particularly Auto-CAD.', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'it-scholarship-programme', 'standard', 'new', NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2019-09-11 11:06:53', '2019-10-24 09:49:29'),
(8, 'Selected Candidates List & Time Schedule for Aptitude Test of IT Scholarship Programme (Round-44)', NULL, 'selected-candidates-list-time-schedule-for-aptitude-test-of-it-scholarship-programme-round-44', '<blockquote><strong>Selected Candidates List &amp; Time Schedule for Aptitude Test of IT Scholarship Programme (Round-44)</strong></blockquote>\r\n<p><img style=\"width: 100%;\" src=\"http://www.idb-bisew.org/images/stories/Intake/r44/Apt_R44_Dhk.jpg\" /></p>', NULL, 'Selected Candidates List & Time Schedule for Aptitude Test of IT Scholarship Programme (Round-44)', NULL, 'publish', '2019-09-15 11:39:00', 'it-scholarship-programme', 'standard', 'off', 'photos/shares/Posts/2019-09/1568693602-15.jpg', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1, '2019-09-15 11:39:19', '2019-10-24 09:37:02'),
(9, '5 Vocational Trade 1271 Sucessfull Graduates', NULL, '5-vocational-trade-1271-sucessfull-graduates', '<p>IDB-BISEW is targeting a particularly neglected and vulnerable section of the student population of the country. These are the students of underprivileged background who fail to progress from high school to the HSC levels.</p><p><br></p>', NULL, 'IDB-BISEW is targeting a particularly neglected and vulnerable section of the student population of the country. These are the students of underprivileged background who fail to progress from high school to the HSC levels.', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'it-scholarship-programme', '1-column-2-row', 'from_old', 'http://project.test/photos/shares/2019-09/15_1567675841.jpg', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 1, 1, '2019-09-16 08:33:35', '2019-09-19 06:06:44'),
(10, 'Placement Record of IT Scholrship Programme', NULL, 'placement-record-of-it-scholrship-programme-124', '<p>The IDB-BISEW IT Scholarship Project was launched in 2003 with the aim of enhancing the employment prospects of meritorious Muslim youths who come from financially disadvantaged background.<br></p>', NULL, 'The IDB-BISEW IT Scholarship Project was launched in 2003 with the aim of enhancing the employment prospects of meritorious Muslim youths who come from financially disadvantaged background.', NULL, 'publish', NULL, 'it-scholarship-programme', '1-column-2-row', 'new', 'photos/shares/Posts/2019-10/1570360085-dark.jpg', 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, 0, 1, '2019-09-16 09:53:42', '2019-10-06 11:08:06'),
